<h1>Guild Charter</h1></td><td>
<hr width="200" size="5" noshade="noshade" color="#f0f0f0" align="center"></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p class="def">Conviction: N
<br> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1: an unshakable belief in something without need for proof or evidence.</p>
<p align="left"> Founded upon the triune principles of family-type bonds, game enjoyment, and
personal excellence, Conviction is a group of tight-knit people that seek to
explore all aspects of the Everquest world without a rabid devotion to
all-night raiding and everyday zerg festivals. We will remain true to one
another and to our mission of honing our individual skills to their very utmost
so that we can advance through Everquest with the satisfaction of
knowing that advancement was earned through teamwork and shared spirit. We will
always stress <b>quality</b> over quantity. We value people above loot. We value unity
above self-aggrandizement. We value tactics above blind force. These are the
convictions that we hold to be true.<br>
<br> The guild is comprised of many different people, each bringing unique and
valuable skills to the whole. We come from a varied background of different
guilds, where the need to find something which fit our own ideas of game play
were not fulfilled. Our convictions drove us together to form something new.
Conviction is one of the newer guilds on the server and has already become a
haven for many similarly-minded people. People who have lent it strength in
addition to the handful that originally felt driven to found it.<br>

<br> Conviction is first and foremost a raiding based guild.  We have currently defeated the
Dragons of Norrath expansion including Yar'Lir, Rikkukin, Kessdona, and Vishimtar.  Progression
through the Depths of Darkhollow is now Conviction's primary focus, having beaten 4 of the 5 Trials to access the Demi-plane. We continue to farm Anguish, and expect that Overlord Mata Muram will soon fall to the hand of Conviction.  We
currently raid every week night, Monday through Friday.  Weekends are left as off days for grinding,
adventuring, and questing, and are always free of any guild event obligations.
<br>
<br> Conviction is a DKP based guild.  Our official loot and DKP/RP type policy is posted on the forum. Links
to the DKP system are availalable as well, for those who have registered and
received approval. <br></p></div>
